{"type":"message","id":"9c5d9d47","parentId":"34bf5186","timestamp":"2026-03-18T23:52:19.385Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_UnvBxr7j7HH5S2phRpdDbrWj","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# HEARTBEAT.md - Periodic Tasks\n\nHeartbeat prompt:\n`Read HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.`\n\n## Core Rules\n\n- `HEARTBEAT.md` 只保留调度规则；长说明放到 `checklists/`\n- 如果没有新情况，回复 `HEARTBEAT_OK`\n- 晚上 `23:00-08:00` 非紧急情况保持安静；**安静不等于停工**，夜间默认应优先静默执行不需要用户确认的内部任务（如回测、下载、校验、整理、生成报告、同步、备份）\n- 若当天已推送且无新增数据，避免重复打扰\n- 只有三类情况主动汇报：\n  1. 新文件/报告已落地\n  2. 脚本已跑出结果\n  3. 需要用户输入/授权\n\n## Scheduled Work\n\n### 1) Workspace backup\n- 频率：每天一次\n- Checklist: `checklists/heartbeat-workspace-backup.md`\n\n### 2) Quant ops\n- 盘前强检：交易日 `09:20-09:40`\n- 日常审计 / 增强 / 实盘面板：每天一次 heartbeat 内执行\n- Checklist: `checklists/heartbeat-quant-ops.md`\n\n### 3) Self-improvement\n- 频率：每天下午或晚间一次\n- Checklist: `checklists/heartbeat-self-improvement.md`\n\n## Quiet / Alert Rules\n\n### 保持安静\n- 非交易日且无异常\n- 当天任务已完成且无新增结果\n- 刚检查过且没有变化\n\n### 主动提醒\n- 盘前强检失败\n- 每日策略审计为 `ALERT`\n- 双源验证/热力图失败\n- 实盘面板生成失败或需要权限\n- self-improvement 有新提升项或新技能草稿\n\n## Memory Maintenance\n\n每隔几天可以在 heartbeat 中做一次：\n- 复盘最近 `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`\n- 将稳定结论提升到 `MEMORY.md`\n- 清理过期信息\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773877939383}}
{"type":"message","id":"230696c3","parentId":"9c5d9d47","timestamp":"2026-03-18T23:52:34.293Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering heartbeat tasks**\n\nThe user is asking about whether anything needs attention and suggests I respond with HEARTBEAT_OK. I might need to check the checklist files for scheduled tasks, especially since the prompt mentions long explanations in those checklists. It’s still early morning, so I should decide if I need to perform the scheduled tasks now or if I can wait. However, if there's nothing new or noteworthy, perhaps the HEARTBEAT will still be okay. I'll check relevant artifacts or scripts, but I shouldn’t repeat old tasks from prior chats.**Deciding on heartbeat response**\n\nI can simply respond with HEARTBEAT_OK if nothing needs attention, as it indicates there's no immediate concern. However, I wonder if I should check for any alerts from previous tasks, even though I shouldn't infer from old tasks. Given that it's before the scheduled windows and quiet hours, and there are no evident alerts, I'm leaning towards just replying with HEARTBEAT_OK. I need to ensure I keep my response clean—final response will be exactly HEARTBEAT_OK.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"HEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773877939386}}
