{"type":"message","id":"9ba9016d","parentId":"581009c2","timestamp":"2026-03-19T00:23:04.117Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating maintenance tasks**\n\nI’ve only run the mainline guard, not the audit or enhancements dashboard. I need to think about whether I should execute those as part of the heartbeat since they’re scheduled daily. The internal tasks are more than eight hours, and it's not quiet before 8:00. Also, the workspace backup should happen daily; it only needs to be proactive if there are new files or results. \n\nAfter checking git status, it seems like I have uncommitted changes that should be committed. Though it’s safe internally, pushing externally might need some consideration!**Assessing workspace safety**\n\nUnder AGENTS, it seems like the background maintenance and git hygiene within the workspace are safe. However, my workspace is located at /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace, while the repo root is at /.openclaw. I should check for any sensitive information since the backup checklist says to confirm there are no secrets. Given that git status shows credentials and secrets directories are untracked, there might be sensitive items, so I shouldn't commit. Do I need to report this? Only if user input or authorization is needed, perhaps.**Planning skills and audits**\n\nI’m considering if I need to scan for skills that might help with self-improvement. It seems like none are really applicable right now, so I'm not identifying any specific skills to focus on. I think running a daily strategy audit and enhancements could be useful, possibly generating a dashboard too. I’m thinking about using multi-tool parallel processing for the audit and enhancements, considering if they can run independently. Let’s make sure to allow enough timeout.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"先把 heartbeat 里要求的日常量化巡检跑完，再按结果决定是安静还是告警。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_D3E7jKU7Bj4P4hEJIDOCbyJR","name"