{"type":"message","id":"eb94fe41","parentId":"3a3a2d55","timestamp":"2026-03-19T03:28:56.379Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Inspecting message mirroring**\n\nI’m looking into whether there’s a feature to mirror outbound messages to the session transcript but not across different channels. I’ve found some mirror options, but it looks like they apply to the transcript rather than syncing between channels. I think it would be useful to inspect the sessions.json file for session keys and source channels. I’ll parse the relevant session entries using Python to get the right details.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"我把会话索引也拆一下，确认网页端和飞书是不是落在了两个不同 session。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9LBk4vsHUCIZ8jU0bDV6O7xw","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport json, pathlib\np=pathlib.Path('/Users/ling/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json')\nobj=json.loads(p.read_text())\nitems=[]\nfor x in obj if isinstance(obj,list) else obj.get('sessions',[]):\n    key=x.get('key') or x.get('sessionKey')\n    if not key: continue\n    if 'feishu' in key or key=='agent:main:main':\n        items.append({k:x.get(k) for k in ['key','kind','channel','to','sourceChannel','sourceChannelRaw','sourceTo','sourceToRaw','deliveryContext','updatedAt','label'] if k in x})\nprint(json.dumps(items[-20:], ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\nPY","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773890916494}}
